Function Reference/save mod rewrite rules « WordPress Codex
-----------

Updates the htaccess file with the current rules if it is writable.

Always writes to the file if it exists and is writable to ensure that we
blank out old rules.

Usage
-----

` <?php save_mod_rewrite_rules(  ); ?> `

Change Log
----------

Since: [1.5](/Version_1.5 "Version 1.5")

Source File
-----------

`save_mod_rewrite_rules()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/misc.php`

